{"lemma":"سَكِينَةٌ","slug":"سَكِينَةٌ","root":"س.ك.ن","root_slug":"س-ك-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَكِينَة","root":"سكن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20265"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inner peace, tranquility, calmness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"presence of God, shechinah","examples":[{"text":"هُوَ ٱلَّذِىٓ أَنزَلَ ٱلسَّكِينَةَ فِى قُلُوبِ ٱلْمُؤْمِنِينَ","english":"He is the One Who sent down serenity upon the hearts of the believers."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of سِكِّين (sikkīn, “knife”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"An Arabic formation from the root س ك ن (s k n), but religious meanings are a semantic loan from Hebrew שְׁכִינָה (shəḵīná)."},"ipa":["/sa.kiː.na/","/sik.kiː.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20265","headword_ar":"سَكِينَةٌ","root":"skn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sik~iynapN","text_ar":"سِكِّينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sak~iynapN","text_ar":"سَكِّينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,) mentioned in the “ Nawádir, ” (Msb,) on the authority of AZ, (L,) but of a measure of which there is no [other] known instance, (L, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Calmness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravity, staidness, steadiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sedateness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a quality inspiring reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veneration:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mercy, pity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compassion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanN","text_ar":"سَكَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aid"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"victory"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conquest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing whereby a man is calmed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillized:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) pl. of the first word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakaAy^inu","text_ar":"سَكَايِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har p. 62.) One says of a man who is calm or tranquil, or grave &c.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi Als~akiynapu","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ السَّكِينَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon him is"},{"kind":"text","text":"resting, or abiding,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calmness"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (L.) And it is said in a trad., respecting the Prophet, on the occasion of the coming down of revelation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faga$iyatohu Als~akiynapu","text_ar":"فَغَشِيَتْهُ السَّكِينَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And calmness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillity, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayobap","text_ar":"غَيْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., as here used,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absence of mind from self and others by its being exclusively occupied by the contemplation of divine things"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And in the Kur [ii. 249], it is said, [with reference to the coming of the ark of the covenant,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi sakiynapN mino rab~ikumo","text_ar":"فِيهِ سَكِينَةٌ مِنْ رَبِّكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In which shall be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of your becoming tranquil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy in your minds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] when it cometh to you ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from your Lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Zj, L, K:) or, as some say, there was in it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a head like that of the cat; when it uttered a cry, victory betided the Children of Israel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing having a head like that of the cat"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a tail like that of the cat"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd)],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of chrysolite and sapphire, and a pair of wings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an image like the cat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"that was with them among their forces,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the appearance of which their enemies were routed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an animal having a face like that of a human being, compact"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rest thereof being unsubstantial like the wind and the air:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the images of the Prophets, from Adam to Mohammad:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the signs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"miracles, with the performance of which Moses was endowed, and to which they trusted so as to be easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiet, in their minds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbuwt","text_ar":"تَابُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":"to which these words refer is meant the heart, [or rather the chest, i. e. bosom,] and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"skynp","text_ar":"سكينة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge, and purity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincerity, in the heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bosom"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Bd.) In a trad. of' Alee, respecting the building. of the Kaabeh, it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^arosala A@ll~`h A_ilayohi Als~akiynapa","text_ar":"فَاَرْسَلَ ا@للّٰه اـِلَيْهِ السَّكِينَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And God sent to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wind swift in its passage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","K","Ks","Zj","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}